(379, 191, 'panels_data', 'a:3:{s:7:"widgets";a:2:{i:0;a:4:{s:5:"title";s:0:"";s:4:"text";s:1735:"<h1>Camden Capital Welcomes Monte I. Resnick​</h1>\n\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Palm Beach, September 2013 – Camden Capital announces the appointment of Mr. Monte Resnick as Managing Director. Mr. Resnick is establishing the firm’s wealth management business throughout Florida. He is actively involved in portfolio management selection as a member of the firm’s Investment Committee.\n</p><p style="text-align: justify;">\nMr. Resnick brings over 24 years of extensive wealth advisory experience to Camden Capital. Prior to joining, he served as an Executive Director with JP Morgan and was a Vice President within Neuberger Berman’s private wealth group, where he maintained a leadership role in Florida for several years. His investment management career started with Wall Street research firm Sanford Bernstein.\n</p><p style="text-align: justify;">\n“Monte is a perfect fit for Camden Capital,” said CEO and Founder, John Krambeer. “He has a stellar reputation in south Florida, not only as a trusted wealth management executive, but also as an active civic contributor and leader on several nonprofit boards and committees.”\n</p><p style="text-align: justify;">\nCamden Capital provides unbiased investment advice and legacy planning to high-net-worth individuals and families. With a focus on developing long-term relationships with its clients, the firm has grown exclusively through referrals. Camden’s relentless commitment to achieving its clients’ objectives, exclusive investment access and consolidated performance and tax reporting are at the core of its value proposition.</p>\n\n<a class="btn" title="BACK TO RECOGNITION" href="http://192.168.1.86/camdencapital/recognition/">BACK TO RECOGNITION</a>";s:6:"filter";s:1:"1";s:4:"info";a:4:{s:4:"grid";s:1:"0";s:4:"cell";s:1:"0";s:2:"id";s:1:"0";s:5:"class";s:14:"WP_Widget_Text";}}i:1;a:4:{s:5:"title";s:0:"";s:4:"text";s:146:"<di