e Technology and Camden Capital.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">From 1991 through 2002 Mr. Nicklaus played golf professionally on both the PGA and European Tours. Mr. Nicklaus is an accomplished golf course designer, with courses throughout the United States and abroad, including Wales, Mexico and Spain.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Mr. Nicklaus is Co-Chairman of the Children’s Healthcare Charity, Inc., a non-profit organization and primary beneficiary of the Honda Classic, a premier PGA Tour event. Mr. Nicklaus received a bachelor’s degree in Business Administration, with a Major in Finance, from The Ohio State University.</p>\n<h3>Merlin E. Robertson</h3>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Mr. Merlin Robertson spent his profession working with global investment management companies in the high- to ultra-high net worth space.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">He held distinguished positions at Merrill Lynch, Eastman Dillon, Winthrop, Trust Company of the West and Capital Guardian Trust. While at Capital Guardian Trust, Mr. Robertson was in charge of marketing and institutional sales throughout the Midwestern region with clients such as Notre Dame, University of Chicago and John Deere.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">He was the President of the Los Angeles Bond Club and is a graduate of the University of Southern California with a B.S. in Finance.</p>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a title="About" href="http://192.168.1.86/camdencapital/about/">OVERVIEW</a></p>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a title="Leadership" href="http://192.168.1.86/camdencapital/about/leadership/">LEADERSHIP</a></p>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a title="Board" href="http://192.168.1.86/camdencapital/about/board/">BOARD</a></p>', 'Board', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'board', '', '', '2014-06-27 15:38:14', '2014-06-27 15:38:14', '', 13, 'http://localhost:81/www/camdencapital/?page_id=17', 0, 'page', '', 0),
