(142, 1, '2014-06-27 15:35:40', '2014-06-27 15:35:40', '<h3>John M. Krambeer</h3>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Mr. John Krambeer is the Founder and Chief Executive Officer of Camden Capital. He is actively involved in managing client relationships while overseeing the investment management process, including manager selection and review.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Mr. Krambeer has spent his career working with both traditional and alternative investment managers, evaluating asset allocation strategies, managing long-term equity portfolios and implementing options strategies for large concentrated stock positions.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Prior to forming Camden Capital, Mr. Krambeer spent 16 years at Merrill Lynch, where he and his wealth management team built the firm’s largest Private Banking and Investment Group. Mr. Krambeer has been featured in several wealthmanagement industry publications for his expertise in the independent investment advisory world and his insight on current market conditions.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Mr. Krambeer serves as a Trustee for the Autry National Center and is very active in the community, supporting various philanthropic organizations. He was an inaugural member of the Schwab Institutional Advisory Council for Advisors Turning Independent (ATI) - an elite sounding board for firms transitioning to independence in the ever-changing wealth management industry. Mr. Krambeer received a B.S. in Finance from Woodbury University.</p>\n<h3>Gary T. Nicklaus</h3>\n<p style="text-align: justify">Mr. Gary Nicklaus  is Vice Chairman of the Board of Directors of the Nicklaus Companies ("Nicklaus").  Nicklaus is an innovative global organization that has been investing throughout the world for decades, including spending the last 25+ years transacting business in China.  Mr. Nicklaus is a member of the Board of Directors of companies in numerous sectors including Medical Technology, Cloud Computing, NearShore Technology and Camden Capital.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify">From 1991 through 2002 Mr. Nicklaus played golf professionally on both the PGA and European Tours. Mr. Nicklaus is an accomplished golf course designer, with courses throughout the United States and abroad, including Wales, Mexico and Spain.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify">Mr. Nicklaus is Co-Chairman of the Children’s Healthcare Charity, Inc., a non-profit organization and primary beneficiary of the Honda Classic, a premier PGA Tour event. Mr. Nicklaus received a bachelor’s degree in Business Administration, with a Major in Finance, from The Ohio State University.</p>\n<h3>Merlin E. Robertson</h3>\n<p style="text-align: justify">Mr. Merlin Robertson spent his profession working with global investment management companies in the high- to ultra-high net worth space.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify">He held distinguished positions at Merrill Lynch, Eastman Dillon, Winthrop, Trust Company of the West and Capital Guardian Trust. While at Capital Guardian Trust, Mr. Robertson was in charge of marketing and institutional sales throughout the Midwestern region with clients such as Notre Dame, University of Chicago and John Deere.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify">He was the President of the Los Angeles Bond Club and is a graduate of the University of Southern California with a B.S. in Finance.</p>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a title="About" href="http://192.168.1.86/camdencapital/about/">OVERVIEW</a></p>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a title="Leadership" href="http://192.168.1.86/camdencapital/about/leadership/">LEADERSHIP</a></p>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a title="Board" href="http://192.168.1.86/camdencapital/about/board/">BOARD</a></p>\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;', 'Board', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '17-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-27 15:35:40', '2014-06-27 15:35:40', '', 17, 'http://192.168.1.86/camdencapital/17-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
